11:33.894 --> 11:35.896
I don't get it, every
time I do everything right,

11:35.929 --> 11:37.164
everything go wrong.

11:37.197 --> 11:39.032
You think you did
everything right?

11:39.066 --> 11:41.368
Bro, if you're trying
to lecture me right now, don't.

11:41.401 --> 11:42.702
You don't know what it's like.

11:42.736 --> 11:44.471
I got this kid coming.
Hey.

11:46.139 --> 11:47.841
ANDRE:
Yeah, you got it
pretty rough, Hakeem.

11:47.875 --> 11:49.943
I guess I just had it easy, man.
Dre, you know...

11:49.977 --> 11:51.711
No, no, no, let's just
baby the baby boy, okay?

11:51.745 --> 11:53.580
You know, I mean,
I lost my kid, right?

11:53.613 --> 11:56.283
But let's just
pamper Hakeem again.

11:56.316 --> 11:57.885
Bro, that's not what
I'm trying to say.

11:57.918 --> 12:00.287
It's just right now I just suck
at every point of life.

12:00.320 --> 12:02.222
He really does.

12:02.255 --> 12:03.723
Seriously.

12:03.757 --> 12:05.926
(laughter)
I'm sorry.

12:05.959 --> 12:08.561
I guess in your own
ass-backwards way,

12:08.595 --> 12:10.730
you had a sort of
impressive run.

12:10.764 --> 12:12.465
Mm-hmm.

12:12.499 --> 12:15.235
That's true, man, you was a wild
CEO, but you were making moves.

12:15.268 --> 12:18.038
Yeah, a mash-up
between DMX and Bill Gates.

12:18.071 --> 12:19.606
(laughter)

12:21.674 --> 12:24.711
Mom needs us, guys.

12:24.744 --> 12:25.979
All right,
ASAs are important to her,

12:26.013 --> 12:28.748
and that's enough to
make me want to help.

12:28.782 --> 12:30.717
Dre, this is weird to me,
though.

12:30.750 --> 12:34.287
You, of all people, doing
a bipolar event for Lucious.

12:34.321 --> 12:36.089
Look, it's not for him,
it's for Mom.

12:36.123 --> 12:38.425
I'm starting to feel like that's
the same thing these days.

12:38.458 --> 12:40.760
Wait, are you saying Mom
is falling for Lucious?

12:40.794 --> 12:42.462
Hell no.

12:42.495 --> 12:45.232
I ain't getting King Kong
and Godzilla back together.

12:45.265 --> 12:46.900
Look at it like this, Hakeem,

12:46.934 --> 12:48.902
if you think that you deserve
a shot at getting Laura back,

12:48.936 --> 12:50.737
shouldn't, shouldn't
Lucious get a shot

12:50.770 --> 12:52.739
at getting Cookie back?

12:52.772 --> 12:55.075
And, Jamal, you know,
you-you wanted an ASA

12:55.108 --> 12:56.776
since you were in diapers.

12:56.810 --> 12:59.079
You gonna let Lucious
knock you off your game?

12:59.112 --> 13:00.180
Whatever, Dre.

13:00.213 --> 13:01.915
(laughter)

13:01.949 --> 13:03.917
You know there
was a time when Dad

13:03.951 --> 13:05.752
would have
called you a sissy,

13:05.785 --> 13:07.287
and you would
have gone running

13:07.320 --> 13:10.157
and crying
to Aunt Carol.

13:10.190 --> 13:13.626
I don't think that's
who you are anymore.

13:17.364 --> 13:20.333
*

13:20.367 --> 13:22.169
JAMAL: Look at this,

13:22.202 --> 13:23.803
Mom and Andre got me ho'ing
for Lucious and this charity.

13:23.837 --> 13:25.005
(scoffs) As usual.

13:26.039 --> 13:28.208
Some things never change.

13:29.709 --> 13:31.011
Hey, Becky.
Oh...

13:31.044 --> 13:33.113
Hey, Michael.
Jamal.

13:33.146 --> 13:36.483
I, uh, I work
for the event caterer.

13:37.817 --> 13:38.952
But, I mean,
if that's not cool with you...

13:38.986 --> 13:41.288
Nah, nah, nah, it's cool.

13:41.321 --> 13:42.655
It's-it's a good gig.

13:42.689 --> 13:44.191
Wouldn't want you to lose out.

13:44.224 --> 13:46.293
So, are we going to discuss

13:46.326 --> 13:47.794
this whole
Chase One thing?
Becky.

13:47.827 --> 13:48.896
'Cause I never got...

13:50.197 --> 13:53.666
Okay.
I'll see you later, Michael.

13:53.700 --> 13:55.502
See you, Becky.

13:57.204 --> 14:00.840
I saw a clip of that press event
you did a couple nights ago.

14:00.874 --> 14:02.209
Yeah.

14:02.242 --> 14:03.810
Lucious looked like
he was getting ready

14:03.843 --> 14:05.178
to punch your lights out.

14:05.212 --> 14:08.315
It's so twisted,
and all the politics

14:08.348 --> 14:10.350
got me wanting to snap.

14:10.383 --> 14:13.853
Um, I have a break
in a couple minutes,

14:13.887 --> 14:15.355
if you want to talk.

14:17.057 --> 14:19.559
But if you don't, it's fine.
I want to.

14:19.592 --> 14:21.794
Michael.

14:23.931 --> 14:25.698
("Better Man" by Leon Bridges
playing)

14:28.068 --> 14:30.503
* I don't want much...

14:30.537 --> 14:33.373
Look at this place.

14:33.406 --> 14:36.076
It hasn't changed one bit,

14:36.109 --> 14:38.411
since that night we met.

14:38.445 --> 14:40.847
I remember that night.

14:40.880 --> 14:43.250
It's one of my first,
like, real performances.

14:43.283 --> 14:46.053
Mm-hmm. And you didn't tell
anyone in your family.

14:46.086 --> 14:48.021
Hell no. (laughs)

14:48.055 --> 14:51.891
(band playing slow ballad)

14:51.925 --> 14:55.262
I mean, look at them.
I miss that, man.

14:55.295 --> 14:57.530
You see how
they're not concerned

14:57.564 --> 15:00.367
with show business politics?

15:00.400 --> 15:02.102
It's just about real music.

15:02.135 --> 15:04.771
And they don't care whether this
was a stadium or a coffeehouse.

15:04.804 --> 15:07.874
They'd probably sing on
the street if they had to.

15:07.907 --> 15:09.876
Jamal Lyon is in the house.

15:09.909 --> 15:11.544
Why don't you come
up here and join us?

15:11.578 --> 15:12.579
Come sit in.

15:12.612 --> 15:13.780
Nah, man, I love y'all.

15:13.813 --> 15:14.914
I'm gonna...
I'm-a just watch.

15:14.948 --> 15:17.384
It's all good.

15:17.417 --> 15:21.221
* Hmm hmm hmm hmm

15:21.254 --> 15:24.992
* Hmm hmm
hmm hmm *

15:26.593 --> 15:29.629
* Lost in a crowd

15:29.662 --> 15:33.800
* You feel your
thoughts out loud *

15:33.833 --> 15:38.071
* Lost in the wilderness
of the sound *

15:38.105 --> 15:42.409
