don't drown *

15:42.442 --> 15:44.244
* Life, it goes fast

15:44.277 --> 15:46.613
* Youth is gone

15:46.646 --> 15:48.781
* Feelings of loss, come on

15:48.815 --> 15:50.917
* Grieve, move on

15:50.950 --> 15:52.785
* Stuck in the shadows

15:52.819 --> 15:55.255
* Of a lie

15:55.288 --> 15:57.324
* That you tried

15:57.357 --> 16:00.927
* To leave behind...

16:00.960 --> 16:03.096
Come on, Jamal!

16:03.130 --> 16:05.298
Come on, man,
get up onstage here.

16:05.332 --> 16:07.967
Jamal Lyon.

16:14.974 --> 16:16.976
* Sounds so good,
don't you agree? *

16:20.647 --> 16:22.782
* Yeah

16:22.815 --> 16:24.851
* No, no

16:24.884 --> 16:27.454
* Well, we travel

16:27.487 --> 16:29.456
* And we travel

16:29.489 --> 16:33.326
* Trying to find it

16:33.360 --> 16:35.862
* I know that
neither one of us *

16:35.895 --> 16:37.964
* Oh, neither one of us

16:37.997 --> 16:41.468
* Can survive it

16:41.501 --> 16:44.137
* We're just people

16:44.171 --> 16:46.473
* Lonely people

16:46.506 --> 16:51.144
* You and I

16:51.178 --> 16:52.379
* Come on

16:52.412 --> 16:53.513
* Get yo self

16:53.546 --> 16:54.647
* Get yo self

16:54.681 --> 16:55.715
* Get yo self

16:55.748 --> 16:56.816
* Get yo self

16:56.849 --> 16:58.017
* Get yo self

16:58.051 --> 17:01.321
* Get yo self together

17:01.354 --> 17:05.192
* No, no, no, no, no,
no, no, no, no, no! *

17:17.270 --> 17:19.372
Hi. Come on in.

17:19.406 --> 17:22.875
Welcome to
baby wonderland.

17:22.909 --> 17:25.044
Yeah.

17:25.078 --> 17:27.347
Look, I hired
the bossest baby-proofers.

17:27.380 --> 17:29.416
No edges,
no corners, no sockets.

17:29.449 --> 17:31.451
It's like a baby wonderland now.

17:33.720 --> 17:35.888
I even got something
for the nursery.

17:36.889 --> 17:38.891
(growls)

17:40.560 --> 17:42.862
(sighs)
What are you doing, Hakeem?

17:42.895 --> 17:44.597
I'm the father.

17:44.631 --> 17:46.566
I know it's more
than buying stuff,

17:46.599 --> 17:48.268
but it's to show you
that I'm in.

17:50.403 --> 17:52.205
What about your fiancée?

17:52.239 --> 17:54.741
What about her?

17:54.774 --> 17:56.042
I love her.

17:56.075 --> 17:57.577
She loves me.

17:57.610 --> 18:00.380
And I know
she'll love the baby, too.

18:00.413 --> 18:01.714
But before I step to her,

18:01.748 --> 18:05.452
I got to make sure
we straight first.

18:06.919 --> 18:09.055
(sighs) Well, what makes you
think that I want you involved

18:09.088 --> 18:10.957
in raising our child?

18:10.990 --> 18:12.892
Anika,

18:12.925 --> 18:14.727
the one good thing
about being a Lyon--

18:14.761 --> 18:18.064
other than being
kicked up to the fullest--

18:18.097 --> 18:21.100
is that I've seen every
wrong move in raising a family,

18:21.134 --> 18:23.236
and I know what I shouldn't do.

18:23.270 --> 18:26.473
But there's a problem.

18:26.506 --> 18:29.642
Your father threatened my life
the day the baby is born.

18:29.676 --> 18:30.777
What?

18:30.810 --> 18:33.246
So forgive me if I'm not feeling

18:33.280 --> 18:34.981
the whole concept
of being a Lyon.

18:37.817 --> 18:39.752
WAITRESS: Next we have
the chocolate ganache gâteau

18:39.786 --> 18:40.920
with fresh raspberries.

18:40.953 --> 18:42.922
Enjoy.
Thank you.

18:42.955 --> 18:44.424
Well, seriously,

18:44.457 --> 18:46.092
your-your staff was telling me

18:46.125 --> 18:48.261
that this series I'm doing
on you keeps getting bigger.

18:48.295 --> 18:50.297
Well, if you move me
to your front page,

18:50.330 --> 18:52.665
maybe I'll give you
an exclusive.

18:52.699 --> 18:55.602
You'd make it exclusive for me,
Lucious?

18:55.635 --> 18:57.103
Exclusively yours.

18:57.136 --> 18:58.771
Hmm.

18:58.805 --> 19:01.441
Okay, well, I guess
we'll have to go front page.

19:01.474 --> 19:03.310
Mmm, my God.

19:03.343 --> 19:04.444
This woman has
a tracking device

19:04.477 --> 19:05.678
in your sack
or something.

19:05.712 --> 19:09.015
This woman got
a lot of things, honey.

19:09.048 --> 19:10.683
Ooh, it smell
fishy in here.

19:10.717 --> 19:12.819
We were eating lobster
for lunch.

19:12.852 --> 19:14.321
Mmm, I'm sure.

19:14.354 --> 19:16.623
I'm free tonight.

19:16.656 --> 19:18.124
How about I have
my dessert later?

19:18.157 --> 19:20.460
(chuckles) I'll send the car.
All right.

19:20.493 --> 19:23.863
You might want to send
some vinegar and water.

19:23.896 --> 19:25.031
I'll see you
tonight, Lucious.

19:25.064 --> 19:27.334
Why you got
to be so nasty?

19:27.367 --> 19:28.535
COOKIE:
You the one nasty.

19:28.568 --> 19:30.136
You need to
disinfect this seat.

19:30.169 --> 19:32.138
(laughs)
What?

19:32.171 --> 19:33.506
Your boy got something
really important

19:33.540 --> 19:34.874
to say to you, Lucious.

19:34.907 --> 19:36.843
So you threatened
to kill her.

19:36.876 --> 19:38.345
The mother of my child?

19:41.013 --> 19:43.015
I don't know what
you're talking about.

19:43.049 --> 19:46.152
The last I heard, you didn't
care what happened to her.

19:46.185 --> 19:47.554
Her mom's telling her
to leave New York

19:47.587 --> 19:49.322
and to get as far away
from me as possible.

19:49.356 --> 19:51.824
Oh, well,
she can't do that, Hakeem.

19:51.858 --> 19:54.827
You have rights as a father,
and we have lawyers.

19:54.861 --> 19:57.196
Hell, Thirsty's shady ass
can get that baby.

19:57.230 --> 19:58.498
Mom, stop.

19:58.531 --> 19:59.666
I'm the father.

19:59.699 --> 20:01.067
The baby's mine, okay?

20:01.100 --> 20:03.670
I want Anika to feel
safe and happy.

20:03.703 --> 20:05.538
So here's the deal:

20:05.572 --> 20:08.007
if Anika leaves,

20:08.040 --> 20:10.743
you won't see
the baby or me again.

20:10.777 --> 20:12.512
Uh, Hakeem.

20:12.545 --> 20:15.415
Hakeem.

20:15.448 --> 20:18.084
Ooh, he's upset.

20:18.117 --> 20:20.920
(chuckles)
You think it's funny, don't you?

20:20.953 --> 20:23.856
You know we need the boy
to show up to our event.

20:23.890 --> 20:26.859
Or you can get used
to answering to whitey.

20:26.893 --> 20:29.896
You know I'm sick and tired
of the way they do business.

20:29.929 --> 20:34.033
I know, so maybe
you should back off

20:34.066 --> 20:37.103
and let me handle boo boo kitty.

20:37.136 --> 20:39.372
You worry about
that-that scallop

20:39.406 --> 20:41.274
you got coming
to see you later.

20:42.509 --> 20:44.711
(sighs)

20:44.744 --> 20:47.414
I should have never went public.

20:50.650 --> 20:52.251
ANDRE:
Being here today

20:52.285 --> 20:55.288
wasn't an easy thing for me.

20:55.322 --> 20:58.891
In fact, it was terrifying.

20:58.925 --> 21:01.661
And that's exactly
why I'm doing it.

21:01.694 --> 21:04.497
Mental health is such
a shameful subject,

21:04.531 --> 21:07.099
especially for
African-American families.

21:07.133 --> 21:09.569
For years, my father
hid from that shame,

21:09.602 --> 21:11.237
because the thought
of his own mother being bipolar

21:11.270 --> 21:12.639
was more than he could bear.

21:12.672 --> 21:14.273
I feel like maybe Lucious

21:14.307 --> 21:15.908
should actually
say that second part,

21:15.942 --> 21:17.276
you know?

21:17.310 --> 21:18.745
"I hid from the shame,"

21:18.778 --> 21:20.413
therefore, it's more
of a back and forth

21:20.447 --> 21:21.748
between father and son,
you know?

21:21.781 --> 21:23.783
Got you.

21:23.816 --> 21:25.418
That's why you're here, baby.

21:25.452 --> 21:28.120
(laughter)

21:29.155 --> 21:32.425
If this gets him
reinstated as CEO,

21:32.459 --> 21:34.461
you know what that means, right?
Yes.

21:34.494 --> 21:36.162
With Jamal and Hakeem
out of the running,

21:36.195 --> 21:38.465
that leaves you solidly
in place for his number two.

21:38.498 --> 21:41.100
Mmm, just a heartbeat
away from the throne, baby.

21:41.133 --> 21:42.435
Where you always belonged.

21:42.469 --> 21:44.303
Yeah, that's right.

21:44.337 --> 21:48.174
And what about those other two
board members, the holdouts?

21:48.207 --> 21:50.777
Oh, they'll be there.
I made sure of that.

21:50.810 --> 21:53.680
Okay, good.
Cookie's arranged
for a ton of press.

21:53.713 --> 21:56.616
Everything's in position.

21:56.649 --> 21:58.050
Okay?

22:00.353 --> 22:02.355
(distant shouting, horn honking)

22:08.995 --> 22:11.364
Anika?

22:11.398 --> 22:13.332
Uh, Anika, we need to talk
about what you're doing

22:13.366 --> 22:14.367
with your baby. (gasps)

22:14.401 --> 22:16.002
Oh, no. What happened?

22:16.035 --> 22:17.169
Step aside, ma'am.

22:17.203 --> 22:18.805
Wait, is she okay?

22:18.838 --> 22:20.139
Ma'am, you need to step aside.

22:20.172 --> 22:21.474
You need to stop
telling me what to do.

22:21.508 --> 22:22.642
Is she gonna be all right?

22:22.675 --> 22:24.644
Hold up. Is she okay?
(gasps)

22:24.677 --> 22:26.646
Look, ma'am, you can
follow us to the hospital.
I'm not following.

22:26.679 --> 22:29.148
I'm riding.
That's my son's baby.

22:29.181 --> 22:31.183
(gasping)

22:37.757 --> 22:40.059
(siren wailing)

22:40.092 --> 22:41.327
Bleeding is dark red,

22:41.360 --> 22:43.830
approximately 100 to 150 cc's.

22:43.863 --> 22:46.699
No visible wounds.
BP is 104/66.

22:46.733 --> 22:48.367
Pulse, 140 beats per minute.

22:48.401 --> 22:50.002
Is she gonna be okay?

22:50.036 --> 22:52.505
Oh, my God, it hurts so bad.

22:52.539 --> 22:54.340
Ma'am, I need you to stay calm.

22:54.373 --> 22:55.708
Can you tell me
how bad the pain is?

22:57.209 --> 22:59.011
She's having
a damn panic attack.

22:59.045 --> 23:00.212
Can't you give
her something?

23:00.246 --> 23:01.380
I can give her oxygen,
that's it.

23:01.414 --> 23:03.082
Pain meds might effect the baby.

23:03.115 --> 23:05.084
No, I'm not...
Anika, no, no,
no, no, no, no, no.

23:05.117 --> 23:06.352
Anika, listen.

23:06.385 --> 23:07.587
Listen, listen.

23:07.620 --> 23:10.189
Anika, I need you
to relax, okay?

23:10.222 --> 23:11.558
You're stressing the baby.

23:11.591 --> 23:13.059
I can't.

23:13.092 --> 23:16.429
Look, uh, I know you're scared.

23:16.463 --> 23:18.698
I need you to trust me
right now, okay?

23:18.731 --> 23:20.700
Forget everything.
Forget everything.

23:20.733 --> 23:22.535
And just listen to
the sound of my voice.

23:22.569 --> 23:24.236
Breathe.

23:24.270 --> 23:25.538
Breathe with me.

23:25.572 --> 23:28.941
Like this:
(breathing steadily)

23:28.975 --> 23:30.076
Come on.

23:30.109 --> 23:32.244
There you go.

23:32.278 --> 23:33.880
Come on, keep going.

23:33.913 --> 23:35.882
Okay, let him put that on.

23:35.915 --> 23:37.049
Keep breathing.

23:37.083 --> 23:39.752
That a girl.

23:42.088 --> 23:44.056
Yes, you're gonna
be all right.

23:44.090 --> 23:48.394
And that baby's gonna be
just fine, believe that.

23:48.427 --> 23:50.730
Thank you.

23:50.763 --> 23:54.634
Besides, Hakeem would kill me if
something happens to his baby.

23:54.667 --> 23:56.769
You mean your grandchild.

23:56.803 --> 23:58.805
(siren wailing)

24:00.172 --> 24:02.174
(R&B song playing softly)

24:12.284 --> 24:15.488
* La, la, la, la

24:15.522 --> 24:18.424
* La, la,
la, la *

24:18.457 --> 24:19.859
Mmm.

24:19.892 --> 24:23.262
(chuckles)

24:23.295 --> 24:25.998
You like that?
Uh...

24:26.032 --> 24:28.501
The Whitney's been
trying to get me

24:28.535 --> 24:31.437
to part with that
for a decade.

24:31.470 --> 24:32.805
You should donate it.

24:32.839 --> 24:36.342
Art is supposed
to be shared.

24:36.375 --> 24:40.146
Well, I share my music
and my words.

24:50.322 --> 24:52.458
Oh, I like this.

24:52.491 --> 24:54.460
(laughs)

24:54.493 --> 24:58.330
You really shut the
whole club down for me?

24:58.364 --> 25:01.467
You sure Cookie's not
gonna bust in on us?

25:01.500 --> 25:03.035
Nah.

25:03.069 --> 25:06.005
This is a place
for demons tonight.

25:09.909 --> 25:11.911
Mm-hmm.
Oh, you like it.

25:13.012 --> 25:14.647
Just show me.

25:14.681 --> 25:15.882
Gettin' rough with me?

25:15.915 --> 25:16.849
But I'm on top.

25:16.883 --> 25:17.984
You like that?

25:18.017 --> 25:18.918
Yeah, what do you think?

25:25.892 --> 25:29.361
There you are.

25:29.395 --> 25:30.529
Do you like that?

25:30.563 --> 25:31.764
Only if you mean it.

25:33.132 --> 25:34.533
Come here.

25:41.373 --> 25:42.508
Do you feel that?

25:42.541 --> 25:43.843
I see you like
to be in charge, huh?

25:43.876 --> 25:45.044
Mm-hmm.

25:45.077 --> 25:47.880
I got a job for you.

25:49.215 --> 25:50.182
(chuckles)

25:50.216 --> 25:53.119
You are blowing my mind.

25:53.152 --> 25:54.286
(laughs)

25:54.320 --> 25:56.689
(both moan)

25:56.723 --> 25:58.024
(phone ringing)

25:58.057 --> 25:59.458
Hold on.
Uh-uh.

26:00.760 --> 26:03.095
Come on, not now, Cookie.
Come on, not now.

26:03.129 --> 26:04.864
No, Cookie, damn it.

26:04.897 --> 26:06.866
I'm so sorry.

26:06.899 --> 26:09.535
(scoffs)
It's okay, Lucious, I get it.

26:09.568 --> 26:11.537
(sighs)

26:11.570 --> 26:13.239
You two have a thing.

26:13.272 --> 26:16.208
Cookie says jump,
you ask how high.

26:16.242 --> 26:18.544
Oh, it's not like that.

26:18.577 --> 26:20.046
(sighs)
It's a family emergency.

26:20.079 --> 26:21.914
I will make it up to you.

26:21.948 --> 26:23.783
We'll rain check, you know.

26:24.984 --> 26:27.553
You know,

26:27.586 --> 26:30.422
why don't I do my profile
on Cookie, instead?

26:30.456 --> 26:32.558
"Meet the Manipulative Bitch

26:32.591 --> 26:34.093
"That Has
the Mighty Lucious Lyon

26:34.126 --> 26:35.394
Wrapped around
Her Little Finger."

26:35.427 --> 26:36.562
What do you think?

26:36.595 --> 26:38.998
I think...

26:39.031 --> 26:41.067
you'd do really good

26:41.100 --> 26:43.936
not to say nothing bad
about her ever again.

26:45.772 --> 26:49.241
I'll have Thirsty send a car.

26:49.275 --> 26:51.911
HAKEEM: I get it
if you want to give it back,

26:51.944 --> 26:53.913
but I wish you wouldn't.

26:53.946 --> 26:56.148
I don't know what
my options are.

26:56.182 --> 26:58.918
I mean, at this point.

26:58.951 --> 27:00.920
My options are bad, too,

27:00.953 --> 27:02.955
but you want me to
turn my back on my baby?

27:02.989 --> 27:05.291
It's not fair
to ask me that, Hakeem.

27:05.324 --> 27:06.993
I didn't create the situation.

27:07.026 --> 27:09.095
(phone ringing)
I know you didn't,

27:09.128 --> 27:12.832
but, babe, I got to step up
or I'm gonna look less of a man.

27:12.865 --> 27:14.801
And I wouldn't be worthy
of marrying you.

27:14.834 --> 27:17.937
(ringing continues)

27:17.970 --> 27:19.605
Do you think you
should get that?

27:19.638 --> 27:22.441
Nothing else matters
when I'm with you.

27:22.474 --> 27:25.111
If you're gonna raise
a child with Anika,

27:25.144 --> 27:26.645
where does that leave us?

27:26.679 --> 27:28.848
It'd be my kid.

27:28.881 --> 27:31.283
She'd be the mother,

27:31.317 --> 27:32.618
and you'll be my wife.

27:32.651 --> 27:35.321
We'll be a family.

27:38.657 --> 27:41.660
I think you and me

27:41.694 --> 27:46.665
have very different ideas
of what family means.

27:49.368 --> 27:52.038
Don't do that.

27:52.071 --> 27:53.505
It's done.

28:01.513 --> 28:03.515
(phone ringing)

28:16.295 --> 28:18.697
(elevator bell dings)
COOKIE: Hakeem.

28:18.731 --> 28:19.866
Where is she at?
Is she okay, Mom?

28:19.899 --> 28:20.900
Her mother's right there.

28:23.702 --> 28:26.005
Hi, Mrs. Calhoun,
I'm Hakeem.

28:26.038 --> 28:27.239
It's about time you showed up.

28:27.273 --> 28:28.741
Look, I came as soon as I heard.

28:28.775 --> 28:31.710
My daughter has been pregnant
for almost five months.

28:31.744 --> 28:34.680
Look, I did... I'm sorry.
Can I just go please see her?

28:34.713 --> 28:36.682
(sighs)

28:36.715 --> 28:38.184
Uh, look, he's trying
to do the right thing.

28:38.217 --> 28:39.852
Give him a chance.

28:39.886 --> 28:42.889
Your family isn't exactly known
for doing the right thing.

28:42.922 --> 28:45.424
HAKEEM: Look, Mrs. Calhoun,
I can promise you,

28:45.457 --> 28:47.526
whatever happened in the past,

28:47.559 --> 28:49.461
I'm gonna take care
of Anika and our baby.

28:51.898 --> 28:53.032
Room 348.

28:53.065 --> 28:54.266
She wants to see you.

29:00.973 --> 29:02.608
NURSE: And if you need anything,
hit that button.

29:02.641 --> 29:04.210
Thank you, Linda.

29:04.243 --> 29:05.912
Look at the
grandmas over there.

29:05.945 --> 29:08.614
Boy, shut your damn mouth.

29:08.647 --> 29:10.249
Didn't you hear the nurse?
You got to be quiet.

29:10.282 --> 29:12.084
The baby can't have
all that noise.

29:12.118 --> 29:14.586
It is kind of ironic, though.

29:17.123 --> 29:18.124
(phone chirps)

29:18.157 --> 29:21.127
Uh, Lucious is on his way.

29:21.160 --> 29:22.228
I didn't know

29:22.261 --> 29:23.462
if he'd show up.

29:23.495 --> 29:26.132
Lucious Lyon
is not welcome here.

29:26.165 --> 29:27.733
Not after what he did.

29:27.766 --> 29:30.236
Mom.

29:30.269 --> 29:32.138
What'd he do? Ma?

29:32.171 --> 29:33.272
What, boy?

29:33.305 --> 29:34.406
It's your father.

29:34.440 --> 29:36.075
What hasn't he done?

29:36.108 --> 29:37.810
Look, I'm hungry.

29:38.444 --> 29:40.612
What'd he do?

29:42.648 --> 29:44.483
(elevator bell dings)

29:48.454 --> 29:50.322
Hey, I'm looking
for Anika Calhoun's room.

29:50.356 --> 29:51.958
(clears throat)

29:56.462 --> 29:57.930
How is she?

29:57.964 --> 29:59.966
We need to talk.

30:03.035 --> 30:04.770
Look, son, I'm sorry.

30:04.803 --> 30:06.038
I'm calling off the dogs, okay?

30:07.806 --> 30:09.575
That's my little grandchild
in there.

30:10.576 --> 30:12.811
What you did to Anika's father.

30:12.845 --> 30:16.115
Having him sign those papers
so I can take my company public?

30:16.148 --> 30:17.616
Having him commit fraud?

30:17.649 --> 30:19.785
Oh, so now
you the moral compass.

30:19.818 --> 30:22.454
Just a couple months ago,

30:22.488 --> 30:24.623
you tried to take
my company from me.

30:24.656 --> 30:25.992
People do a whole
lot of stuff

30:26.025 --> 30:27.326
to gain their wealth.

30:27.359 --> 30:29.128
But you know what?

30:29.161 --> 30:31.130
I forgive you for that.

30:31.163 --> 30:32.831
I actually respect you for that.

30:34.533 --> 30:35.968
I thought you was gonna kill me.

30:36.002 --> 30:38.470
A couple times
I thought about it.

30:38.504 --> 30:40.572
If you had been
somebody else's kid, I would.

30:40.606 --> 30:41.640
(chuckles)

30:41.673 --> 30:44.543
But seein' the way

30:44.576 --> 30:47.546
you came into my office
and you stood up for your baby

30:47.579 --> 30:49.581
and your baby's mama...

30:51.683 --> 30:53.819
(sighs)

30:53.852 --> 30:56.022
...I realized I raised
you right.

30:56.055 --> 30:57.990
You understand it's about

30:58.024 --> 31:00.993
family first,
then it's kingdom.

31:01.027 --> 31:02.394
That's the thing,
the family stuff

31:02.428 --> 31:04.230
is a little messed up right now.
Let me guess,

31:04.263 --> 31:07.733
she's really
not feeling this whole

31:07.766 --> 31:10.236
addition to
the nuclear family, huh?

31:10.269 --> 31:13.539
I bet you if you and
I talked to her together,

31:13.572 --> 31:15.942
she would see things
a whole different way.

31:20.212 --> 31:22.281
All right, I'm gonna
go check on Anika.

31:22.314 --> 31:24.050
Make sure she cool.

31:24.083 --> 31:25.584
But you still can't come in.

31:25.617 --> 31:27.219
Respect that.

31:27.253 --> 31:29.755
I'll just sit back here
and make a couple phone calls.

31:29.788 --> 31:33.592
See about making sure
my grandchild and the baby mama

31:33.625 --> 31:35.394
got the best care possible.

31:35.427 --> 31:38.564
There's benefits
to being Lucious Lyon's son.

31:46.238 --> 31:50.709
Mm-mm, you sure are
a snake charmer.

31:50.742 --> 31:52.578
Speaking of which,
your little snake

31:52.611 --> 31:54.380
must have been doing
some slithering.

31:54.413 --> 31:56.415
I smell cheap perfume.

31:56.448 --> 31:58.217
That's said by a woman
that apparently

31:58.250 --> 32:00.286
has no
emotional attachment to me.

32:00.319 --> 32:02.388
Just for your information,

32:02.421 --> 32:05.624
nothing happened
between me and Harper.

32:05.657 --> 32:08.094
You know,
they got blue pills for that.

32:08.127 --> 32:10.462
Nothing to be ashamed of.

32:10.496 --> 32:11.964
The day I need one
of them blue pills

32:11.998 --> 32:14.600
is the day I'm gonna
buy the damn company.

32:16.935 --> 32:19.905
I really don't care
what did or did not happen

32:19.938 --> 32:21.807
between you and mop head.

32:21.840 --> 32:26.612
You know, truth is,

32:26.645 --> 32:28.914
she just didn't do it for me.

32:28.947 --> 32:31.750
I like a smart woman,

32:31.783 --> 32:35.121
but I like a woman
that got some hood in her.

32:35.154 --> 32:37.756
Yeah, well,
she's too skinny to be hood.

32:37.789 --> 32:40.592
You know I like a woman
that's got some curves to her.

32:40.626 --> 32:41.793
Oh, yeah?

32:41.827 --> 32:43.329
You had her.

32:43.362 --> 32:45.097
Should've kept her.

32:45.131 --> 32:47.766
Uh, if you roll your way
over here...

32:47.799 --> 32:50.102
Uh...

32:50.136 --> 32:52.104
What if I could get you

32:52.138 --> 32:54.940
an exclusive profile
in the trades?

32:54.973 --> 32:57.776
Something that could go online
as early as tomorrow morning?

32:57.809 --> 33:01.947
That would be
a really good look.

33:01.980 --> 33:04.450
Are you really talking
about scooping Harper?

33:04.483 --> 33:07.153
I mean, you got
a problem with that?

33:07.186 --> 33:08.987
I don't owe her anything,

33:09.021 --> 33:11.323
and she ain't got nothing on me.

33:16.062 --> 33:17.629
LUCIOUS:
I mean, the truth is,

33:17.663 --> 33:20.132
I wanted to put a human face
to mental illness.

33:20.166 --> 33:21.667
That's what
"Boom Boom Boom Boom"

33:21.700 --> 33:23.669
was all about for me, you know?

33:23.702 --> 33:25.804
You're gonna win
that ASA, Lucious.

33:25.837 --> 33:28.207
And that'll be great
for Empire's share price.

33:28.240 --> 33:31.043
I'm sorry for being
so bottom line about it.

33:31.077 --> 33:33.045
Uh-uh, no, you can't
apologize for that.

33:33.079 --> 33:34.480
I mean, that's the difference

33:34.513 --> 33:36.715
between me
and my other son, Jamal.

33:36.748 --> 33:38.384
I'm an artist,
but I actually care

33:38.417 --> 33:39.985
about our shareholders.

33:40.018 --> 33:41.853
Now, I'm not saying

33:41.887 --> 33:43.655
that he is any less
deserving of an ASA

33:43.689 --> 33:44.990
just because me and his mama

33:45.023 --> 33:47.059
picked all his songs
for his album.

33:47.093 --> 33:50.496
No, he's just, uh, an artist
that's still developing,

33:50.529 --> 33:51.830
which is a good thing.

33:51.863 --> 33:53.199
A really good thing.
Nice.

33:54.533 --> 33:57.169
Jamal, we was just
talking about you.
Yeah.

33:57.203 --> 33:59.004
So this is what
we're gonna do, Dad?

33:59.037 --> 34:00.506
For an award?

34:00.539 --> 34:02.908
I came here to support
you and Dre.

34:02.941 --> 34:05.344
Relax, man, I'm just doing
a little business here.

34:05.377 --> 34:07.113
I don't like the way
that you do business.

34:08.714 --> 34:10.716
It's not right.

34:10.749 --> 34:12.017
Jamal.

34:12.050 --> 34:13.185
No, it's cool.

34:13.219 --> 34:14.353
I wouldn't perform here
if you paid me.

34:14.386 --> 34:17.022
I'm out.
Jamal.

34:17.055 --> 34:18.357
You bastard.

34:18.390 --> 34:20.592
Letting another publication
scoop me?

34:20.626 --> 34:22.394
And you knew that
that would make

34:22.428 --> 34:25.030
my big Lucious Lyon
exclusive useless.

34:25.063 --> 34:29.201
I didn't know anything,
sweetheart, but...

34:29.235 --> 34:31.870
(chuckles)
I like to share my stories.

34:31.903 --> 34:33.939
Mm-hmm.

34:36.242 --> 34:37.976
I'll see you later.

34:39.745 --> 34:41.079
No love?

34:47.819 --> 34:50.222
Andre, just the man
I was looking for.

34:50.256 --> 34:51.923
I have something I think

34:51.957 --> 34:53.225
that might interest you.

34:53.259 --> 34:54.626
Um, it's not really a good time.

34:54.660 --> 34:56.094
I'm about to go onstage
with my father.

35:03.769 --> 35:05.070
What is this?

35:05.103 --> 35:07.072
It's a group home
outside of Philadelphia.

35:07.105 --> 35:08.807
This couple

35:08.840 --> 35:10.075
collects money from the state

35:10.108 --> 35:13.011
to take care
of ten mentally ill adults.

35:14.112 --> 35:17.249
Keep going.

35:17.283 --> 35:19.318
That woman's name
is Leah Walker.

35:22.521 --> 35:24.323
I believe
she's your grandmother.

35:27.826 --> 35:29.528
You can keep the pictures.

35:30.496 --> 35:31.663
Hey.

35:31.697 --> 35:33.932
What's going on?
You okay?

35:33.965 --> 35:36.134
Um...

35:36.168 --> 35:37.436
I have to go.

35:37.469 --> 35:38.804
Go?

35:38.837 --> 35:40.138
Go where, babe?

35:48.814 --> 35:51.016
LAURA: Hi.

35:52.150 --> 35:54.353
Laura, what are
you doing here?

35:54.386 --> 35:56.955
Your dad called me.

35:56.988 --> 35:59.291
He said he had Anika moved
to a nicer room

35:59.325 --> 36:02.461
and that you're really
taking care of her.

36:02.494 --> 36:05.163
He said you're becoming
a man he respects.

36:05.197 --> 36:06.832
My dad said that?

36:10.202 --> 36:12.971
Is she gonna be okay?

36:13.004 --> 36:14.873
Yeah, she's doing better.

36:14.906 --> 36:17.376
They say she should be
able to leave tomorrow.

36:25.417 --> 36:27.819
I've been carrying this ring
ever since you took it off.

36:27.853 --> 36:31.390
I was hoping

36:31.423 --> 36:34.926
maybe you could see things
the way I see them.

36:56.582 --> 36:59.585
(indistinct conversation)

37:02.554 --> 37:05.056
(crowd cheering)

37:05.090 --> 37:07.526
Freda, what you doing here?

37:07.559 --> 37:09.861
What up?
What you do...
What you doing here?

37:09.895 --> 37:11.863
I seen your post on Hakeem's
app, thought I'd come through.

37:11.897 --> 37:14.533
That's so dope, come on.
Yeah, yeah, come on, come on.

37:14.566 --> 37:15.867
What's up, y'all?
How y'all doin'?

37:15.901 --> 37:17.736
That is so dope,
you came through?

37:17.769 --> 37:20.906
Yeah, man, had to, man.

37:20.939 --> 37:22.107
(chuckles)

37:22.140 --> 37:24.042
Amen. That's-that's right.

37:24.075 --> 37:25.043
You see, Empire

37:25.076 --> 37:26.945
is a family brand.

37:26.978 --> 37:28.213
And together,

37:28.246 --> 37:30.616
we're taking that brand
into the future.

37:30.649 --> 37:32.718
Together, we've faced
many obstacles

37:32.751 --> 37:34.553
and overcome many challenges;

37:34.586 --> 37:36.822
that's made us
stronger than ever.

37:36.855 --> 37:38.089
Yes.

37:39.758 --> 37:42.394
Where are your sons tonight?

37:42.428 --> 37:45.431
This doesn't really seem
like much of a family.

37:46.765 --> 37:48.233
COOKIE: Uh, you want
to hear about family?

37:48.266 --> 37:51.069
Well, I will tell you
about family.

37:51.102 --> 37:52.571
Ladies and gentleman,

37:52.604 --> 37:54.306
I have an amazing announcement

37:54.340 --> 37:55.407
for you tonight.

37:55.441 --> 37:57.609
For the first time ever,

37:57.643 --> 38:00.412
the Lyon family
will be performing

38:00.446 --> 38:03.248
at this year's ASA awards.

38:03.281 --> 38:06.251
The Empire presents

38:06.284 --> 38:08.420
the first
family of music.

38:08.454 --> 38:10.989
Hakeem, Jamal, and Lucious Lyon,

38:11.022 --> 38:12.424
all on the same stage

38:12.458 --> 38:13.925
at the same damn time.

38:13.959 --> 38:15.761
How about that?

38:15.794 --> 38:17.329
Ain't that something?
Yes.

38:17.363 --> 38:19.631
Is that really gonna happen?
Yes, even if I have

38:19.665 --> 38:21.166
to get a strap

38:21.199 --> 38:23.802
and strangle
you all to behave.

38:25.504 --> 38:27.606
MAN:
The ASAs wanted him,

38:27.639 --> 38:28.874
but we got him.

38:28.907 --> 38:30.308
Ladies and gentleman,

38:30.342 --> 38:32.944
let's give a warm
round of applause

38:32.978 --> 38:35.614
for Jamal Lyon.

38:35.647 --> 38:37.416
(applause and cheering)

38:39.985 --> 38:41.620
BECKY:
Get 'em, Mal!

38:41.653 --> 38:43.288
Okay, Mal!

38:43.321 --> 38:46.091
That's right, Jamal!

38:52.398 --> 38:54.666
Hey!

38:55.667 --> 38:57.202
(funk song begins)

